Escape room "The Submarine" by Escape the Room Texas in Houston
review: I do not post this review lightly. My family and I decided to add this room to our list of experiences and we all wish that we hadn't. The game master did not keep up with us and often gave clues that we had already passed. Many of the puzzles were not reset correctly and the story was disjointed at best. In fact, there were key elements that made 0 sense at all. We left this experience wishing that we had saved our money...

room_title: Escape room "The Submarine" by Escape the Room Texas in Houston
review: Played The Submarine last night. Great action and room. Good job. Will definitely be back again!

room_title: Escape room "The Submarine" by Escape the Room Texas in Houston
review: We had a great time celebrating our son's birthday at Escape the Room in The Woodlands. It was a fun activity that the whole family could enjoy. We managed to beat the clock and escape the Submarine before we ran out of air.

room_title: Escape room "The Submarine" by Escape the Room Texas in Houston
review: Great escape room! We survived the submarine and had a blast! We will return and do another room!

room_title: Escape room "The Submarine" by Escape the Room Texas in Houston
review: We had a great time! Our team worked great together and beat the clock! We conquered the Submarine roo. Thanks to the staff for being so pleasant to your customers.

room_title: Escape room "The Submarine" by Escape the Room Texas in Houston
review: Did the Submarine and had a lot of fun. Escaped with only a few minutes to spare with 3 people. That room says for 8 people but I would not recommend doing it with more than 4-5. 4 would have been perfect for us but with 3 we still got out.
